Some residents in parts of Ekurhuleni are without water. This after a booster station fed by the Eskom grid, experienced a total power supply failure, which affected Vlakfontein water Reservoir that supplies the city. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some residents in parts of Ekurhuleni are without water. READ: SA's water crisis | Nelson Mandela Bay runs risk of running dry This after a booster station fed by the Eskom grid, experienced a total power supply failure which affected Vlakfontein Water Reservoir that supplies the city. Attempts to repair the transformer were unsuccessful.